docs.abstract: Reince Priebus, the president’s first White House chief of staff, said his tenure was even more arduous than outsiders knew. “Take everything you’ve heard and multiply it by 50,” he says in a new book.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The meeting, to say the least, had not gone well. Upset at a presidential dressing down, Attorney General Jeff Sessions had just left the White House vowing to resign. Reince Priebus, the White House chief of staff, raced out of the building, found him in his car, banged on the door and implored him to come back inside.

headline.main: Riding an Untamed Horse: Priebus Opens Up on Serving Trump
headline.print_headline: Take What You Heard ‘And Multiply It by 50’
